Sentencas: Double perovskite material PrBa0.9K0.1Fe1.9Zn0.1O5+delta (PBKFZ) has been designed using the first-principle calculations and synthesized as a new cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Novel mixed H+/e-/O2- conducting cathode material PrBa0.9K0.1Fe1.9Zn0.1O5+δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The influence of K-doping on the crystal structure, structure stability, thermal expansion behavior, electronic conductivity, proton uptake, and electrochemical performance has been investigated.
Titulo: Novel mixed H+/e-/O2- conducting cathode material PrBa0.9K0.1Fe1.9Zn0.1O5+δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: PBKFZ presents the P4/mmm space group, and its thermal expansion coefficient is 16.110(-6) K-1.
Titulo: Novel mixed H+/e-/O2- conducting cathode material PrBa0.9K0.1Fe1.9Zn0.1O5+δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen vacancy concentrations and proton uptake capacity of PrBaFe1.9Zn0.1O5+delta (PBFZ) in wet air (5% H2O) are significantly improved with K doping.
Titulo: Novel mixed H+/e-/O2- conducting cathode material PrBa0.9K0.1Fe1.9Zn0.1O5+δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cell with the PBKFZ cathode shows an excellent electrochemical performance with a peak power density of 1.4 W cm(-2) and polarization resistance of 0.06 omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C, which is significantly higher than that of the cell using the pristine PBFZ cathode.
Titulo: Novel mixed H+/e-/O2- conducting cathode material PrBa0.9K0.1Fe1.9Zn0.1O5+δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This study provides a new and rational strategy to design a high-performance cathode for proton-conducting SOFCs.
Titulo: Novel mixed H+/e-/O2- conducting cathode material PrBa0.9K0.1Fe1.9Zn0.1O5+δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
